===Proper Noun===

A sport played mainly in [[Ireland]] and by Irish communities in Britain. Gaelic football is a relatively modern game, with it's origins only dating back to the 1700s. It is similar in nature to the ancient game of [[hurling]], but feet and hands are used in preference to a stick, or [[caman]]. A size 5 [[soccer]] ball is used, with teams consisting of 15 players, games lasting 70 minutes, with 3 points for a goal and one point for an over. The governing body for both football and hurling is the [[GAA]].